<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/998: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-29T15:00:00-04:00">June 29, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>407. Your 900, June 25, 10 a.m., Whangpoo Conservancy Board. The
                            Department authorizes you to associate yourself with your other
                            interested colleagues in recommending a settlement of the controversy as
                            suggested in paragraph 2 of your telegram under reference.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>